Haut ab.

2431
02:34:17,296 --> 02:34:18,285
Verschwindet!

2432
02:34:22,335 --> 02:34:24,269
<b><font color="#DF01D7">(AIRPLANE PASSES)</font></b>

2433
02:34:32,010 --> 02:34:33,705
Hang in there, Captain.

2434
02:34:52,264 --> 02:34:53,595
<b><font color="#404040">MAN:</font></b> First squad on me.

2435
02:34:53,665 --> 02:34:54,963
<b><font color="#404040">MAN:</font></b> Drivers,
keep moving.

2436
02:34:55,034 --> 02:34:56,968
Get the 60 set up.

2437
02:34:59,005 --> 02:35:01,235
<b><font color="#404040">MAN:</font></b> See if we can
cut them off.

2438
02:35:01,307 --> 02:35:02,740
<b><font color="#404040">MAN:</font></b>
Clear the intersection!

2439
02:35:19,158 --> 02:35:20,147
Medic!

2440
02:35:23,629 --> 02:35:25,062
Medic!

2441
02:35:25,131 --> 02:35:26,359
We got a medic?

2442
02:35:32,370 --> 02:35:35,306
They're tank-busters,
sir-- P-51s.

2443
02:35:36,909 --> 02:35:38,376
Angels on our shoulders.

2444
02:35:44,617 --> 02:35:45,549
What, sir?

2445
02:35:49,988 --> 02:35:51,820
<b><font color="#404040">MILLER:</font></b> James...

2446
02:35:54,527 --> 02:35:55,858
earn this.

2447
02:36:00,366 --> 02:36:01,298
Earn it.

2448
02:36:30,763 --> 02:36:34,164
<b><font color="#404040">GENERAL MARSHALL:</font></b>
My Dear Mrs. Ryan,

2449
02:36:34,233 --> 02:36:36,667
it's with the most
profound sense of joy

2450
02:36:36,736 --> 02:36:40,137
that I write to inform you
your son,

2451
02:36:40,206 --> 02:36:42,367
Private James Ryan,

2452
02:36:42,441 --> 02:36:44,374
is well and,
at this very moment,

2453
02:36:44,442 --> 02:36:48,003
on his way home from
European battlefields.

2454
02:36:48,079 --> 02:36:51,641
Reports from the front indicate
James did his duty in combat

2455
02:36:51,717 --> 02:36:55,517
with great courage
and steadfast dedication

2456
02:36:55,588 --> 02:36:58,182
even after he was informed
of the tragic loss

2457
02:36:58,257 --> 02:37:01,749
your family has suffered
in this great campaign

2458
02:37:01,827 --> 02:37:05,421
to rid the world of tyranny
and oppression.

2459
02:37:05,497 --> 02:37:08,626
I take great pleasure in joining
the secretary of war,

2460
02:37:08,701 --> 02:37:10,396
the men and women
of the United States Army,

2461
02:37:10,469 --> 02:37:13,597
and the citizens
of a grateful nation

2462
02:37:13,672 --> 02:37:16,266
in wishing you good health
and many years of happiness

2463
02:37:16,342 --> 02:37:19,573
with James at your side.

2464
02:37:19,645 --> 02:37:20,737
Nothing,

2465
02:37:20,813 --> 02:37:24,179
not even the safe return
of a beloved son,

2466
02:37:24,249 --> 02:37:25,648
can compensate you

2467
02:37:25,717 --> 02:37:28,812
or the thousands
of other American families

2468
02:37:28,888 --> 02:37:32,255
who have suffered great loss
in this tragic war.

2469
02:37:32,324 --> 02:37:34,349
And I might share
with you some words

2470
02:37:34,427 --> 02:37:35,917
which have sustained me

2471
02:37:35,995 --> 02:37:37,394
through long, dark nights

2472
02:37:37,463 --> 02:37:40,193
of peril, loss
and heartache.

2473
02:37:40,266 --> 02:37:42,756
And I quote,

2474
02:37:42,834 --> 02:37:44,563
"I pray
that our Heavenly Father

2475
02:37:44,636 --> 02:37:47,834
may assuage the anguish
of your bereavement

2476
02:37:47,907 --> 02:37:50,034
and leave you only
the cherished memory

2477
02:37:50,109 --> 02:37:51,974
of the loved and lost

2478
02:37:52,044 --> 02:37:54,512
and the solemn pride
that must be yours

2479
02:37:54,580 --> 02:37:57,549
to have laid
so costly a sacrifice

2480
02:37:57,616 --> 02:37:59,846
upon the altar of freedom.

2481
02:37:59,919 --> 02:38:02,216
Abraham Lincoln."

2482
02:38:02,287 --> 02:38:04,984
Yours very sincerely
and respectfully,

2483
02:38:05,057 --> 02:38:07,924
George C. Marshall,
General, Chief Of Staff.

2484
02:38:59,244 --> 02:39:02,578
My family
is with me today.

2485
02:39:02,648 --> 02:39:04,513
They wanted
to come with me.

2486
02:39:07,086 --> 02:39:08,747
To be honest
with you,

2487
02:39:08,821 --> 02:39:11,085
I... I wasn't sure
how I'd feel

2488
02:39:11,157 --> 02:39:12,385
coming back here.

2489
02:39:15,127 --> 02:39:18,687
Every day I think about
what you said to me

2490
02:39:18,763 --> 02:39:20,527
that day on the bridge.

2491
02:39:21,967 --> 02:39:24,231
And I've tried
to live my life

2492
02:39:24,303 --> 02:39:26,100
the best I could.

2493
02:39:27,173 --> 02:39:29,266
I hope
that was enough.

2494
02:39:30,409 --> 02:39:33,310
I hope that,
at least in your eyes...

2495
02:39:34,980 --> 02:39:36,913
I've earned
what all of you

2496
02:39:36,981 --> 02:39:38,813
have done for me.

2497
02:39:52,198 --> 02:39:53,563
James.

2498
02:39:55,867 --> 02:39:57,995
"Captain
John H. Miller."

2499
02:40:06,445 --> 02:40:09,278
Tell me I've led
a good life.

2500
02:40:09,348 --> 02:40:10,440
What?

2501
02:40:11,684 --> 02:40:14,346
Tell me I'm a good man.

2502
02:40:21,160 --> 02:40:22,821
You are.

